etymology.description: 丣(丣) (yǒu) -> an ancient form of 酉(酉) (yǒu, "wine vessel") -> depicts a wine vessel
etymology.interpretation: 丣(丣) (yǒu) is an ancient form that represents the character 酉(酉) (yǒu, "wine vessel") and depicts a wine vessel. This character was later associated with the concept of alcohol, reflecting its historical context in ancient China.

examples.chinese: 他丣一本好书(他丣一本好書)。
examples.pinyin: Tā yǒu yī běn hǎo shū.

examples.chinese: 太阳出来时(太陽出來時)，树林中丣一片祥和(樹林中丣一片祥和)。
examples.pinyin: Tàiyáng chūlái shí, shùlín zhōng yǒu yī piàn xiánghé.
examples.english: When the sun rises, the forest exudes a peaceful atmosphere.

examples.chinese: 时间丣奇妙(時間丣奇妙)。
